103
00:06:20,188 --> 00:06:22,787
Then, what brings you here?

104
00:06:22,788 --> 00:06:25,987
Well, I work for a rival magazine company,

105
00:06:25,988 --> 00:06:29,587
so I thought I'd come and report on your phony, stupid interview.

106
00:06:29,588 --> 00:06:32,287
Of course, I won't let you put on a scenario

107
00:06:32,288 --> 00:06:35,587
to make this non-existent Kamaitachis seem like it exists.

108
00:06:35,588 --> 00:06:36,688
They do exist.

109
00:06:37,588 --> 00:06:39,787
I saw a Kamaitachi!

110
00:06:39,788 --> 00:06:42,487
I saw it running on the water of the hot spring.

111
00:06:42,488 --> 00:06:43,787
Is that true?

112
00:06:43,788 --> 00:06:46,787
Yes! I went after it

113
00:06:46,788 --> 00:06:49,187
but I can't run on water so...

114
00:06:49,188 --> 00:06:52,187
But, more than that it seemed like I was put under a magic spell

115
00:06:52,188 --> 00:06:54,887
or something and couldn't move, so I drowned.

116
00:06:54,888 --> 00:06:58,587
When I woke up, I was drenched and sleeping in the corridor.

117
00:06:58,588 --> 00:06:59,788
Oh.

118
00:07:00,288 --> 00:07:01,987
My, Kohei!

119
00:07:01,988 --> 00:07:03,287
What are you doing?

120
00:07:03,288 --> 00:07:04,987
Oh, Mom!

121
00:07:04,988 --> 00:07:07,587
Did you finish decorating your room already?

122
00:07:07,588 --> 00:07:09,587
You're inviting your friends over tomorrow

123
00:07:09,588 --> 00:07:11,587
