the river-child case

266
00:14:01,704 --> 00:14:04,103
and even the vampire case,

267
00:14:04,104 --> 00:14:08,703
I helped solve all these cases from behind the scene. You know?

268
00:14:08,704 --> 00:14:10,803
If the perp is a Kamaitachi...

269
00:14:10,804 --> 00:14:15,304
It's show time for demon-hunter Yamamura, isn't it?

270
00:14:16,604 --> 00:14:19,403
Well, but in this scientific day and age

271
00:14:19,404 --> 00:14:22,103
when people are talking about going outer space on orbit elevators,

272
00:14:22,104 --> 00:14:25,303
Kamaitachis could never be in existence!

273
00:14:25,304 --> 00:14:28,303
That remark sounds familiar.

274
00:14:28,304 --> 00:14:30,503
Then, please take me to the storeroom

275
00:14:30,504 --> 00:14:34,703
that you say the Kamaitachi attacked you, will you?

276
00:14:34,704 --> 00:14:38,103
I'm sure it's some kind of mistake, though.

277
00:14:38,104 --> 00:14:41,003
He pisses me off! This guy.

278
00:14:41,004 --> 00:14:42,403
I see.

279
00:14:42,404 --> 00:14:46,103
You came to this storeroom to look for the antique sickle.

280
00:14:46,104 --> 00:14:48,503
Then this light bulb suddenly cracked,

281
00:14:48,504 --> 00:14:50,603
and someone in the dark

282
00:14:50,604 --> 00:14:52,903
slashed the back of Mr. Mouri's right hand,

283
00:14:52,904 --> 00:14:56,203
as well as the left arm of you, who speaks in the Osaka dialect.

284
00:14:56,204 --> 00:14:59,203
And lastly, writer Ms. Midori Koyanagi,

285
00:14:59,204 --> 00:15:02,703
you were slashed on your left cheek?

286
00:15:02,704 --> 00:15:03,704
Yes.

287
00:15:03,705 --> 00:15:07,803
Was there anyone back then that was holding some kind of blade?

288
00:15:07,804 --> 00:15:12,503
I was the one holding the sickle back then.

289
00:15:12,504 --> 00:15:16,303
The light bulb cracked just when we found it and I was holding it.

290
00:15:16,304 --> 00:15:20,103
Then, aren't you the one who did it, didn't you?

291
00:15:20,104 --> 00:15:23,303
Didn't you spin that sickle around in the dark?

292
00:15:23,304 --> 00:15:25,903
Idiot! If he flung something like that around,

293
00:15:25,904 --> 00:15:28,103
we wouldn't have gotten away with a wound like this, right?

294
00:15:28,104 --> 00:15:33,503
Then, why don't you check if there was blood on the sickle?

295
00:15:33,504 --> 00:15:35,903
We'll of course check on that.

296
00:15:35,904 --> 00:15:38,503
But maybe there was somebody

297
00:15:38,504 --> 00:15:42,703
who was near the light bulb that could've cracked it?

298
00:15:42,704 --> 00:15:45,704
There could've been, but we weren't watching.

299
00:15:46,804 --> 00:15:49,503
There was nobody near.

300
00:15:49,504 --> 00:15:52,603
Back then, we were by the doorway of the entrance but...

301
00:15:52,604 --> 00:15:55,203
Everybody was looking in on the sickle until

302
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:58,404
just before the sound of the light bulb cracking was heard.

303
00:15:59,804 --> 00:16:02,003
Is this the only light bulb here?

304
00:16:02,004 --> 00:16:03,103
No.

305
00:16:03,104 --> 00:16:05,703
There's another one near the entrance,

306
00:16:05,704 --> 00:16:08,903
but when we got to the storeroom today, it wouldn't turn on.

307
00:16:08,904 --> 00:16:13,403
Come to think of it, this storeroom wasn't locked, was it?

308
00:16:13,404 --> 00:16:17,503
Oh, no. The door itself is old and worn out,

309
00:16:17,504 --> 00:16:21,103
and only old rice grains that were to be disposed of

310
00:16:21,104 --> 00:16:23,403
were stored in here so...

311
00:16:23,404 --> 00:16:26,703
But, you mentioned that the sickle may be worth 10 million yen.

312
00:16:26,704 --> 00:16:30,003
My late husband only happened to say so,

313
00:16:30,004 --> 00:16:34,103
whereas, the Grand Master said it's just a piece of junk.

314
00:16:34,104 --> 00:16:37,503
Just a few days ago, a burglar broke into the storeroom again,

315
00:16:37,504 --> 00:16:41,203
so I was thinking of getting a new door and locking it,

316
00:16:41,204 --> 00:16:43,603
but Grand Master said there's no need for that

317
00:16:43,604 --> 00:16:46,203
because we're in the red.

318
00:16:46,204 --> 00:16:49,403
What did the burglar steal?

319
00:16:49,404 --> 00:16:53,203
It wasn't important enough to even be bothered with.

320
00:16:53,204 --> 00:16:54,903
Ah!

321
00:16:54,904 --> 00:16:57,003
So, this is the sickle in question!

322
00:16:57,004 --> 00:16:58,803
This indeed looks like a sickle

323
00:16:58,804 --> 00:17:00,503
that would be favored and used by an ancient demon,

324
00:17:00,504 --> 00:17:01,803
but all is fine!

325
00:17:01,804 --> 00:17:05,503
I, the demon-hunter Yamamura will arrest it "immedemonly",

326
00:17:05,504 --> 00:17:07,503
so rest assured!

327
00:17:07,504 --> 00:17:09,404
A pun...

328
00:17:10,604 --> 00:17:13,603
What? A Kamaitachi appeared?

329
00:17:13,604 --> 00:17:16,503
How lucky! I wanted to see it too.

330
00:17:16,504 --> 00:17:18,803
Don't say that.

331
00:17:18,804 --> 00:17:21,403
Because some people have gotten hurt, you see.

332
00:17:21,404 --> 00:17:24,203
But, when I almost drowned in the bath,

333
00:17:24,204 --> 00:17:27,503
the one who saved me was probably Kamaitachi.

334
00:17:27,504 --> 00:17:29,703
I wanted to thank it!

335
00:17:29,704 --> 00:17:33,103
By the way, did you finish decorating your room?

336
00:17:33,104 --> 00:17:35,503
Nope, not yet.

337
00:17:35,504 --> 00:17:38,703
I can't do it alone, like Daddy used to do it.

338
00:17:38,704 --> 00:17:42,803
But, I've got a lot of things to do and I can't help you.

339
00:17:42,804 --> 00:17:45,603
Then, would you like us to help you?

340
00:17:45,604 --> 00:17:48,003
Decorating is my cup of tea!

341
00:17:48,004 --> 00:17:49,403
Really?

342
00:17:49,404 --> 00:17:51,003
Thank you.

343
00:17:51,004 --> 00:17:52,203
No problem at all.

344
00:17:52,204 --> 00:17:54,604
-Come on, let's go! -Yes!

345
00:17:55,404 --> 00:17:58,103
How old are you going to be when your birthday comes?

346
00:17:58,104 --> 00:17:59,104
8 years old!

347
00:17:59,105 --> 00:18:01,103
Oh, 8 years old!

348
00:18:01,104 --> 00:18:03,203
Come to think of it, you seem to have been

349
00:18:03,204 --> 00:18:06,203
celebrating your son's birthday quite grandly every year.

350
00:18:06,204 --> 00:18:09,103
I saw it on the website of the inn with photos and all,

351
00:18:09,104 --> 00:18:12,303
Yes, because my husband used to love events.

352
00:18:12,304 --> 00:18:15,003
During a party for my husband's survival game friends,

353
00:18:15,004 --> 00:18:16,403
they got water everywhere

354
00:18:16,404 --> 00:18:18,703
while shooting each other with water guns.

355
00:18:18,704 --> 00:18:20,603
It was really something.

356
00:18:20,604 --> 00:18:24,303
Hey, Kudo, what do you think about this case?

357
00:18:24,304 --> 00:18:28,603
Well, I'm sure that somebody did it in the dark but...

358
00:18:28,604 --> 00:18:31,003
After that everybody's belongings were checked

359
00:18:31,004 --> 00:18:34,103
and yet nobody had anything close to a blade, so...

360
00:18:34,104 --> 00:18:36,303
The weapon was probably...

361
00:18:36,304 --> 00:18:38,503
The debris of cracked glass of the light bulb!

362
00:18:38,504 --> 00:18:41,803
I still can't figure out how the light bulb was cracked,

363
00:18:41,804 --> 00:18:44,603
but there's no doubt that the perp flung around

364
00:18:44,604 --> 00:18:46,603
the cracked pieces of glass of another light bulb

365
00:18:46,604 --> 00:18:48,303
that he had on him to begin with, right?

366
00:18:48,304 --> 00:18:50,303
Yeah. After slashing his targets,

367
00:18:50,304 --> 00:18:52,603
if the cracked pieces were thrown on the floor,

368
00:18:52,604 --> 00:18:54,403
they could make it look like one of the pieces

369
00:18:54,404 --> 00:18:56,304
that was broken off then.

370
00:18:57,004 --> 00:19:01,503
After examining the sickle for blood,

371
00:19:01,504 --> 00:19:03,203
the results determined...

372
00:19:03,204 --> 00:19:05,503
what shall I say...

373
00:19:05,504 --> 00:19:07,804
Nothing was detected!

374
00:19:08,704 --> 00:19:10,703
I guess so.

375
00:19:10,704 --> 00:19:13,103
And? Did you also check the pieces of cracked glass

376
00:19:13,104 --> 00:19:15,203
that were scattered on the floor?

377
00:19:15,204 --> 00:19:18,303
Yeah, there was nothing strange about them, though.

378
00:19:18,304 --> 00:19:20,903
You found no blood on them?

379
00:19:20,904 --> 00:19:23,703
Are you sure you really checked?

380
00:19:23,704 --> 00:19:24,803
Of course!

381
00:19:24,804 --> 00:19:26,503
We picked up all the cracked pieces

382
00:19:26,504 --> 00:19:28,903
and put them back together in their originally form,

383
00:19:28,904 --> 00:19:32,003
but there was no blood anywhere.

384
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:33,303
It can't be.

385
00:19:33,304 --> 00:19:35,103
Then, how?

386
00:19:35,104 --> 00:19:37,203
If there was anything strange...

387
00:19:37,204 --> 00:19:41,803
We found a cigarette butt and chewed gum on the floor.

388
00:19:41,804 --> 00:19:44,903
I think that what happened here is,

389
00:19:44,904 --> 00:19:47,703
an old light bulb cracked on its own

390
00:19:47,704 --> 00:19:50,603
and happened to slash you accidentally when it shattered.

391
00:19:50,604 --> 00:19:54,403
Then we should've felt pain the instant it broke.

392
00:19:54,404 --> 00:19:57,504
But there was a delay between them.

393
00:20:01,104 --> 00:20:03,203
It's... it's the girls' voices!

394
00:20:03,204 --> 00:20:06,003
There was a sound before the scream, wasn't there?

395
00:20:06,004 --> 00:20:08,903
The sound of something cracking and bursting!

396
00:20:08,904 --> 00:20:10,804
Are you all right?

397
00:20:11,704 --> 00:20:13,003
What's wrong?

398
00:20:13,004 --> 00:20:15,903
The lamp suddenly cracked.

399
00:20:15,904 --> 00:20:17,603
Then, the balloons we decorated

400
00:20:17,604 --> 00:20:19,303
started bursting one after the other!

401
00:20:19,304 --> 00:20:21,303
The... there's something...

402
00:20:21,304 --> 00:20:22,904
At this inn after all!

403
00:20:25,004 --> 00:20:27,703
Wasn't that voice the Grand Master's voice?

404
00:20:27,704 --> 00:20:29,503
I think it was.

405
00:20:29,504 --> 00:20:32,003
Don't tell me the Kamaitachi got him?

406
00:20:32,004 --> 00:20:34,103
Where is the Grand Master?

407
00:20:34,104 --> 00:20:37,104
I think at this time, he's at the annex.

408
00:20:39,004 --> 00:20:42,203
Hey! Isn't there a short cut?

409
00:20:42,204 --> 00:20:45,704
It would be fastest to go through the outdoor bath if possible.

410
00:20:48,604 --> 00:20:51,303
No good! Water's still in the tub!

411
00:20:51,304 --> 00:20:54,303
It's not time to clean yet, so...

412
00:20:54,304 --> 00:20:57,203
Is that place on the other side of the fence

413
00:20:57,204 --> 00:20:59,103
where the Grand Master is?

414
00:20:59,104 --> 00:21:01,903
-Yes. -But that fence...

415
00:21:01,904 --> 00:21:04,503
isn't it sort of slightly open?

416
00:21:04,504 --> 00:21:06,603
Kamaitachi!

417
00:21:06,604 --> 00:21:10,703
Just like it rides the wind, it ran over the water!

418
00:21:10,704 --> 00:21:12,904
That's impossible!

419
00:21:14,404 --> 00:21:15,803
There doesn't seem to be

420
00:21:15,804 --> 00:21:18,903
things like transparent plates in the water either.

421
00:21:18,904 --> 00:21:20,603
Isn't there any other way?

422
00:21:20,604 --> 00:21:24,103
Actually the main building and annex are connected by a corridor,

423
00:21:24,104 --> 00:21:26,503
it just happens to be under renovation right now.

424
00:21:26,504 --> 00:21:28,103
It's the long way

425
00:21:28,104 --> 00:21:30,803
but if we go out once and go from the backdoor...

426
00:21:30,804 --> 00:21:32,804
Let's hurry that way then!

427
00:21:38,504 --> 00:21:40,704
That's the annex!

428
00:21:43,904 --> 00:21:46,603
Only our footprints are here, which means...

429
00:21:46,604 --> 00:21:49,404
Nobody passed through here.

430
00:21:51,104 --> 00:21:52,704
Grand Master!

431
00:21:53,904 --> 00:21:55,503
Are you all right?

432
00:21:55,504 --> 00:21:57,703
Please get a light!

433
00:21:57,704 --> 00:21:58,604
Yes!

434
00:22:00,004 --> 00:22:02,304
It won't turn on.

435
00:22:03,704 --> 00:22:05,403
What's with this paper door?

436
00:22:05,404 --> 00:22:07,103
It's torn...

437
00:22:07,104 --> 00:22:09,003
it looks to have been slashed by something.

438
00:22:09,004 --> 00:22:11,004
Hey! Don't tell me!

439
00:23:42,104 --> 00:23:45,903
Then why is there blood on the upper part of the cut?

440
00:23:45,904 --> 00:23:49,704
To make it look like Kamaitachi did it.

441
00:23:50,104 --> 00:23:53,403
The suspect is Kamaitachi.

442
00:23:53,404 --> 00:23:54,703
Don't be silly!

443
00:23:54,704 --> 00:23:56,303
What makes you think that a demon or whatever

444
00:23:56,304 --> 00:23:58,203
will go cracking the glass to by lock

445
00:23:58,204 --> 00:23:59,604
or shut the breaker down?

446
00:24:01,104 --> 00:24:03,703
I see, so that's the story!

447
00:24:03,704 --> 00:24:05,704
That's why back then, that person...

448
00:24:06,204 --> 00:24:07,603
Next Conan,

449
00:24:07,604 --> 00:24:11,704
"Kamaitachi Inn (Part 2)"

